content:
Creating a web page to display a table of data using HTML and CSS involves defining the structure of the table using HTML and styling it with CSS. Here's a step-by-step guide to help you create a simple web page with a table:

### Step 1: HTML Structure

First, you need to create an HTML file and define the basic structure of the table.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Data Table</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Data Table Example</h1>
    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Column 1</th>
                <th>Column 2</th>
                <th>Column 3</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Row 1, Cell 1</td>
                <td>Row 1, Cell 2</td>
                <td>Row 1, Cell 3</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Row 2, Cell 1</td>
                <td>Row 2, Cell 2</td>
                <td>Row 2, Cell 3</td>
            </tr>
            <!-- Add more rows as needed -->
        </tbody>
    </table>
</body>
</html>
```

### Step 2: CSS Styling

Next, create a CSS file named `styles.css` to style the table.

```css
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 20px;
}

h1 {
    text-align: center;
}

table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 20px 0;
}

th, td {
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    padding: 8px;
    text-align: left;
}

th {
    background-color: #f2f2f2;
}

tr:nth-child(even) {
    background-color: #f9f9f9;
}

tr:hover {
    background-color: #f1f1f1;
}
```

### Explanation:

- **HTML**:
  - The `<table>` element is used to create the table.
  - `<thead>` contains the header row with `<th>` elements.
  - `<tbody>` contains the data rows with `<tr>` and `<td>` elements.

- **CSS**:
  - `border-collapse: collapse;` is used to make borders collapse into a single border.
  - `nth-child(even)` selector is used to style alternate rows differently.
  - `:hover` is used to change the background color of a row when the mouse hovers over it.

### Step 3: Viewing the Web Page

To view your table, open the HTML file in a web browser. You should see a neatly styled table displaying your data.

This is a basic example, and you can expand upon this by adding more rows, columns, or additional styling to suit your needs.
